content: Lots of fun play

Downloaded and played for like ten minutes. Usually enjoy Kemco games so I dropped $30 in IAPs. Then the game froze up multiple times. I had to re-download and all my purchases are gone with no ability to recollect LDP or items.
Very fun Zelda like Rpg with turn-based enemy fighting. Worth the money, I enjoy it.
Fun RPG game! Tip:rem to fight the "regret" monster to claim the item(through the collectable menu) to defeat the Serpent boss early in the game

Great game i greatly enjoy the unusual features. My main concerns are research, and finding certaim enemies. Spent 5 hours playing so far and im hoping i get sent back to the first forest at some point. After trying to fill an empty slot for 2 hours i couldnt find and enemy that i havent researched. When viewing the enemies you have research it doesnt show what they can or if they drop anything. So i assume stealing isnt a big goto. I hope to find an encounter rate boost. It wasnt in the shop.
Great game
Good story great game mechanics

Subpar compared to other KEMCO titles. Complaints/Bugs: - Rugal's unison gauge barely moves, but that doesn't matter because you'll kill everything before you even get the chance to use any unison attack. - Whichever character is in the 3rd slot for Unison attacks will never do one unless they initiate it. - Weapon Conversion was nerfed so much it is useless. - Chaining attacks has been virtually eliminated just like in the last Kemco game - Zero customization unlike in other recent Kemco titles

So far its ok. Basically the same as every one of their games with a slightly diff story and characters. Way too much dialog without any choices or interaction. Doesnt have to be meaningful, per se, but there needs to be user input to keep us engaged. As it is, I skip most conversations as they aren't all necessary. It is fun in its current state, just nothing to set it apart from other options.
Love the way u threw me off with the flash back with a review
Game is not playable. It freezes during dialog scenes and I have to close the app every time. I haven't even made it to the first battle.
Good
Enjoyable
Nice

A step below ambition accord, kemco has spoiled me with 3d graphics and I can't go back. The review goading is a little shameless halfway in the game for premium players who bought the game. All I can say for sure is that the relationship system that affects the ending has not been explained in the halfway point. Seems short, 3 artifacts and a super boss maybe. Average kemco controls, missed opportunity with limit break potential that miden's tower had. It's a 3 star game.
Bought this game then all off a sudden there's a free version.. Sheesh

This is a good game, But the dialogue is way to long and drawn out.. it's 15 min of talking and reading and then 4 min of play time before another 15 min of reading and dialogue.. it's great to build the story but this is wayy tooo much!!

While I love a game with challenge, this one had a tendency to freeze during the cutscenes at some points. I would close out the game only to open it up, continue, and have it freeze again. Please fix this. Other than that, I don't mind the challenges of combat.

I'm expecting better games from the developers but it seems that your recent games are far inferior to your previous titles like the Asdivine series (except Kamura), Fernz Gate, Journey to Kriesha, Fanatic Earth, Machine Knight and Band of Monsters. The present games storylines and mechnics are becoming less creative, redundant and boring storyline. I missed the feeling when the first time I played Machine Knight, Journey to Kriesha and Band of Monsters.
Fix it cause it crashes
Fun game Kemco games are the best.
Meh
I like this game

As a Kemco Fan, I will give a minimum of 3 stars 😎 The plot was quite cute but not unique on its own and the comedy that you wanted to be portrayed became less entertaining because of many typos and grammatical errors 😓 Its too much an average plot that even a kid can understand how the story will progress, drama events became dull 😩 The only reason I bought this product was to play with a beautiful heroine like Silky but later on I found out she was a guy, a trap in anime sense... 😭
Great game lots of fun to play and story holds your interest way to go guys!

This game is hard to keep up. The mp usage is extreme even on basic elements and forever leveling up grinding like mad. Even alchemy on the weapons don't get stronger then the next town armor. I died so easy even on auto. I've played almost all other Kemco games and never got to a point on giving up on a $9.00 game and I purchased 21 other games from Kemco only and did good.

I like it but too long dialog. (so it seem to be touch to the character and story line.)

Another great game!!
Pretty good story and interesting cnaracters. Lots of battles to fight if you want all the treasure. Really fun to p!ay.

Bare in mind this is a remake of an older game by exe-create so not the usual new kemco rpg affair here, this is best recommended for those who enjoy the old kemco rpg, however it does have some nice modern touchs and the art style i would love see make a come back later on, its different from the norm and that is great, keep it up, i hope alphadia 3, 4 and 5 may be remade too one day. :)
